## The Metric

Your primary metric is **diligence_coverage** — the percentage of checklist items that are populated with sourced, validated data. Higher is better. Target: 100%.

Secondary metric: **confidence_score** — average confidence across populated items, weighted by item criticality. Each finding gets a confidence score from 0.0 to 1.0 based on source quality, recency, and corroboration. Higher is better. Target: ≥ 0.85.

```
diligence_coverage = (populated_items / total_items) × 100
confidence_score = Σ(item_confidence × item_weight) / Σ(item_weight)
```

After each research cycle, record to `results.tsv`:

```
cycle | timestamp | deal_id | checklist_item | source | confidence | diligence_coverage | confidence_score | notes
```

