## Constraints

1. **Do not modify `program.md`** — this file is your instructions. The human iterates on it.
2. **Do not modify `prepare.py`** — it handles setup and is considered fixed infrastructure.
3. **Do not modify `checklist_template.json`** — it is the master template. Deal-specific copies live in `deals/{deal_id}/`.
4. **Only modify `research.py`** — all your logic changes (new source connectors, extraction improvements, validation rule tweaks, scoring adjustments) go here.
5. **Always cite sources** — every finding must include a source URL, document reference, or API endpoint. Unsourced findings are automatically rejected.
6. **Never fabricate data** — if you cannot find a data point, mark it as `unfilled` or `flagged`. Never hallucinate values. An unfilled checklist item is infinitely better than a wrong one.
7. **Respect source tiers** — do not assign Tier 1 confidence to a Tier 3 source. The confidence score must reflect actual source reliability.
8. **Flag conflicts immediately** — if two sources disagree by >10% on a numeric value or contradict on a binary/enum value, stop and write to `flags/`. Do not silently pick one.
9. **Time budget per item** — spend no more than **10 minutes** per checklist item per cycle. If you cannot resolve it in 10 minutes, flag it and move on. This ensures ~6 items/hour, ~50+ items overnight.
10. **Git discipline** — commit after every successful finding or flag. Commit messages must include deal_id, item_id, and current coverage percentage. Never batch commits.

