## Output: Diligence Package

When `diligence_coverage` ≥ 95% OR all remaining items are flagged, the agent generates a consolidated diligence summary:

```
deals/{deal_id}/
├── DILIGENCE_SUMMARY.md        — Human-readable summary with key findings, flags, and risk items
├── checklist.json              — Fully populated (or flagged) checklist
├── findings/                   — All structured findings
├── flags/                      — All items requiring human review
└── sources/                    — All supporting documents
```

The `DILIGENCE_SUMMARY.md` should follow this structure:

```markdown
# Due Diligence Summary: {property_name}
## Deal: {deal_id} | Date: {date} | Coverage: {X}% | Confidence: {Y}

### Executive Summary
[2–3 sentences: property type, tenant, key metrics, overall risk assessment]

### Key Metrics
| Metric | Value | Source | Confidence |
|--------|-------|--------|------------|
| Building SF | ... | ... | ... |
| In-Place NOI | ... | ... | ... |
| Going-In Cap Rate | ... | ... | ... |
| ... | ... | ... | ... |

### Flags & Open Items
[List all flagged items with discrepancy details and recommended resolution]

### Category Summaries
[One section per checklist category with key findings]

### Risk Matrix
| Risk | Severity | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|----------|------------|------------|
| ... | ... | ... | ... |
```

